    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2020-03-25</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2020-04-16T13:36:22Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>This bill extends the tax credit for health insurance costs to eligible national defense or infrastructure workers. An <em>eligible national defense or infrastructure worker</em> is an individual who was employed in a critical industry as of January 31, 2020, filed for unemployment compensation after such date, and is covered by health insurance. A <em>critical industry</em> is an industry related to critical national infrastructure or national defense&nbsp;and is severely distressed due to COVID-19 (i.e., the coronavirus disease 2019).</p> <p>The bill also extends the tax credit through 2022. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>A bill to amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to expand eligibility for the health care tax credit to workers in certain critical industries.</title>
